.START 

Retail sales volume rose a revised 0.5% in August from July and was up 1% from August 1988, the British Central Statistical Office said. 

For the three months ended in August, retail sales volume was down 1% from the previous three months and up 1.2% from the year-earlier period, unchanged from the provisional estimate. 

The value of retail sales was up about 6% in August from a year ago, also unchanged from the provisional estimate. 

